-- Spanish Stocks: Acerinox, ArcelorMittal, Ebro Foods, Endesa Are Active
-- Francesca Cinelli
-- 2010-08-06T11:28:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-06/acs-banco-espirito-santo-prisa-sol-melia-iberian-equity-market-preview.html

          
          
             Spain’s  IBEX 35 Index  gained for the
first day in three, rising 22.4, or 0.2 percent, to 10,862.4 as
of 1:27 p.m. in Madrid. The gauge has increased 3.4 percent this
week.  
 The following were among the most active stocks in the
Spanish market.  
 Acerinox SA  (ACX SM), the world’s biggest stainless-steel
maker, rose 18 cents, or 1.3 percent, to 13.68 euros as copper,
lead, nickel, tin and zinc prices rose in London.  
 ArcelorMittal  (MTS SM), the world’s biggest steelmaker,
rose for a fifth day, gaining 30 cents, or 1.2 percent, to 25.62
euros.  
 Ebro Foods SA  (EBRO SM) fell for a second day this week,
losing 28 cents, or 2.1 percent, to 13.25 euros as the food and
beverage industry was the worst performer in Europe today
because the price of wheat has soared.  
 Endesa SA  (ELE SM), Spain’s second-largest utility,
declined for a third day, losing 23.5 cents, or 1.2 percent, to
19.25 euros as UBS AG downgraded European utilities to
“neutral.”  Iberdrola Renovables SA  (IBR SM) declined for a
third day, falling 4.1 cents, or 1.5 percent, to 2.69 euros.  
